v1⃗×v2⃗=(y1z2−z1y2z1x2−x1z2x1y2−y1x2)
\vec{v_1} \times \vec{v_2} = \left(
    \begin{array}{c}
      y_1 z_2 - z_1 y_2 \\
      z_1 x_2 - x_1 z_2 \\
      x_1 y_2 - y_1 x_2
    \end{array}
  \right)
​v​1​​​⃗​​×​v​2​​​⃗​​=​⎝​⎛​​​y​1​​z​2​​−z​1​​y​2​​​z​1​​x​2​​−x​1​​z​2​​​x​1​​y​2​​−y​1​​x​2​​​​​⎠​⎞​​
  /**
   * @param {Vector3} v1 
   * @param {Vector3} v2
   * @return {Vector3}
   */
  static cross(v1, v2) {
    return new Vector3(
      v1.y * v2.z - v1.z * v2.y,
      v1.z * v2.x - v1.x * v2.z,
      v1.x * v2.y - v1.y * v2.x
    );
  }

